# UI Color Style: White Background + Colored Borders

Cards, category tiles, and buttons should use **white backgrounds with colored borders** — not solid colored backgrounds.

## Cards & List Items

```html
<!-- ✅ GOOD: white bg, colored border -->
<div
  class="bg-white border-2 rounded-2xl p-5 hover:shadow-md transition-all"
  [style.border-color]="item.color || '#22c55e'"
>
  <div
    class="w-11 h-11 rounded-xl bg-white border-2 flex items-center justify-center"
    [style.border-color]="item.color || '#22c55e'"
    [style.color]="item.color || '#22c55e'"
  >
    <ng-icon ...></ng-icon>
  </div>
  <p class="text-gray-800 font-semibold">Label</p>
  <p class="text-gray-500 text-xs">Description</p>
</div>

<!-- ❌ BAD: solid colored background -->
<div [style.background]="item.color">...</div>
```

## Buttons

```html
<!-- ✅ GOOD: white bg, colored border + text -->
<button class="bg-white border-2 border-emerald-500 text-emerald-600 hover:bg-emerald-50 px-4 py-2 rounded-lg font-medium transition-colors">
  Action
</button>

<!-- ❌ BAD: solid colored button -->
<button class="bg-emerald-600 text-white">Action</button>
```

## Icons

Icons should **never** have a colored background. The icon itself should carry the color.

```html
<!-- ✅ GOOD: white container, colored icon -->
<div
  class="w-11 h-11 rounded-xl bg-white border-2 flex items-center justify-center"
  [style.border-color]="item.color || '#22c55e'"
  [style.color]="item.color || '#22c55e'"
>
  <ng-icon name="lucideTag" size="20"></ng-icon>
</div>

<!-- ❌ BAD: green/colored background on icon container -->
<div class="bg-green-500 ...">
  <ng-icon class="text-white" ...></ng-icon>
</div>
```

- Use `text-gray-800` / `text-gray-500` for text on white backgrounds
- Use `hover:shadow-md` on cards for subtle depth on hover
- Apply the category/brand color only to borders and the icon element itself, never as a background fill
